&lt;p&gt;The solid reproducer, to be run from a Lustre-Client, is very simple :&lt;br/&gt;
======================================================================&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;touch /ccc/work/.../foo&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lfs path2fid /ccc/work/.../foo&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x200002cb4:0x3cbb:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;rm /ccc/work/.lustre/fid/&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x200002cb4:0x3cbb:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; MDS crash like described just before &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
======================================================================&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;indeep crash-dump and concerned source-code analysis clearly indicate that &quot;rm/unlink by-FID&quot; is not fully implemented but also not correctly checked+prohibited !!...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My assumption is that this should be fixed/checked+prohibited with the following :&lt;br/&gt;
==================================================================================&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@gaia1 lustre-2.0.0.1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; # diff -urN lustre/mdd/mdd_dir.c.orig lustre/mdd/mdd_dir.c.bfi&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8212; lustre/mdd/mdd_dir.c.orig	2011-11-04 18:46:46.000000000 +0100&lt;br/&gt;
+++ lustre/mdd/mdd_dir.c.bfi	2012-02-01 17:18:37.074912630 +0100&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -415,7 +415,7 @@&lt;br/&gt;
                                 RETURN(rc);&lt;br/&gt;
                 }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if (mdd_is_append(pobj))&lt;br/&gt;
+                if (mdd_is_immutable(pobj) || mdd_is_append(pobj))&lt;br/&gt;
                         RETURN(-EPERM);&lt;br/&gt;
         }&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@gaia1 lustre-2.0.0.1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; # &lt;br/&gt;
==================================================================================&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think ??&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, our 1st tests with Lustre 2.1.0 show the same problem/behavior ...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
